Answer: The error is occurring because you are modifying the ArrayList while iterating over it using an Iterator. This is not allowed and can lead to unexpected behavior. 

To fix this, you should use a for-each loop instead of an Iterator. The for-each loop does not allow modifications to the underlying collection. 

Here's how you can modify your code:

```java
public void deleteCustomer(){
    String id = null;
    boolean c = false; //true if id is found
    int remember = 0;  //Remembers the deleted index
    id = JOptionPane.showInputDialog(null,"input the id of whome you want to delete", "input id", JOptionPane.PLAIN_MESSAGE);
    int id2 = Integer.parseInt(id); //new int id.
    for(Customer customer : customers){
        if(id2 == customer.getID()){
            customers.remove(customer);
            c = true;
            remember = customers.indexOf(customer);
            break;
        }
    }
    if(c){
        int i1 = JOptionPane.showConfirmDialog(null,"the customer " + customers.get(remember).getName() + " has been deleted.", "input people", JOptionPane.PLAIN_MESSAGE);
    }
    else{
        int i1 = JOptionPane.showConfirmDialog(null,"the customer could not be found, please check your id", "input people", JOptionPane.PLAIN_MESSAGE);
    }
}
```

In this code, we use a for-each loop to iterate over the `customers` ArrayList. We remove the customer from the ArrayList using the `remove(Object o)` method, which removes the first occurrence of the specified element from this list, if it is present. We then break the loop and continue with the rest of the code.

This way, we avoid the `IndexOutOfBoundsException` because we are not modifying the ArrayList while iterating over it.

Please note that this code assumes that the `Customer` class has a `getID()` method that returns the ID of the customer. If this is not the case, you will need to adjust the code accordingly.

Also, please note that the `indexOf(Object o)` method returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified element in this list, or -1 if this list does not contain the element. So, `customers.indexOf(customer)` will give you the index of the removed customer.

